<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-03T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-03T20:00:00-05:00" n="930" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d930">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.3394/239: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Neville</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-04T10:00:00+09:00">September 4, 1936—10
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 4—12:01 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>177. Department’s 225, August 11, 4 p.m. via Shanghai. Japanese Foreign
                            Office by note dated yesterday has informed the Embassy that the
                            Japanese Government has no objection to the proposed visit of the <hi rend="italic">Gold Star</hi> at Miike but regrets it cannot give
                            consent to proposed visits at Truk, Palau and Saipan.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Neville</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>